The United States has strongly condemned the terrorist attack on the Baqir-ul-Olum Mosque in Kabul, Afghanistan. The attack resulted in the death of many innocent civilians and left more than 40 wounded. The U.S. believes that this cowardly act was aimed at fueling sectarian tensions in Afghanistan. The U.S. extends condolences to the victims' families and friends and fully supports efforts to hold those responsible accountable. The U.S. and its international partners are committed to helping Afghanistan build a more stable and peaceful future.